  "summaryLine": "Satyadev shines in a sincere but sluggishly paced drama.",
  "theRead": "Critics widely praise Satyadev's committed, one-man-show performance as a terminally ill man in this 1991-set drama from director Venkatesh Maha. The near-universal knock is pacing: a self-indulgent, overstretched screenplay makes the first half a tiresome slog, and the more purposeful finish only partly redeems it. Reviewers respect the ambition and unconventional storytelling even where the execution drags.",
